    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with **Kyle Tucker** (81.01) serving as our premier offensive anchor. Facing Jack Leiter, **Tucker** benefits from a massive 81.01 efficiency score driven by a favorable SP xERA of 4.43 and a +5% wind-aided boost at his back, making him our highest-upside play for run production. Close behind, **Jackson Merrill** (75.27) is a must-start; he faces a soft matchup against Ryan Feltner and possesses a rare combination of high-efficiency base projections and a specific advantage against a slow-delivery pitcher that boosts his stolen base potential, a critical metric for our roster construction. **Gunnar Henderson** (69.67) also remains a core staple; despite a tough assignment against the elite Logan Webb, **Henderson**\u2019s leadoff positioning and dynamic platoon profile keep his floor safely within the Strong category.\n\nOur strategy heavily favors exploiting specific environmental and matchup edges today. **Miguel Vargas** (63.48) and **Andy Pages** (63.51) are both high-priority starts, with **Vargas** benefiting from favorable wind conditions and **Pages** leveraging a high-SB probability against the slower delivery of Leiter. **Nolan Schanuel** (61.99) and **Luis Robert Jr.** (61.93) are also set to provide significant value against pitchers with elevated xERAs, effectively capitalizing on their respective platoon slots. While **Josh Lowe** (53.66) and **Drake Baldwin** (50.12) are lower on the spectrum, they remain in the lineup to maximize our total game-cap exposure given the overall lack of explosive alternatives on our bench.\n\nThe most difficult decision for the coaching staff today involved **Marcell Ozuna** (51.94), who narrowly missed the starting nine. While **Ozuna**\u2019s base projection is robust, he was outperformed by the situational efficiency of **Heliot Ramos** and the tactical need to prioritize players with higher sprint-speed-to-base-delivery ratios. Furthermore, we elected to sit **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (50.63) today, as his matchup against Joe Ryan presents a high-risk scenario that lowered his net efficiency below that of **Liam Hicks** (51.55), who secures a better platoon-adjusted outcome. Managers should remain vigilant regarding the \"Lineup Pending\" status for **Baldwin**, **Schanuel**, **Polanco**, **Henderson**, **Wilson**, **Vargas**, **Merrill**, **Robert Jr.**, **Ramos**, **Tucker**, **Pages**, and **Lowe**; any unexpected shifts in batting order will require an immediate reassessment of our projected category output.",
